desc: This charm grants you the power to enter the #cUnity Training Center within Mu Lung Dojo# where you #cautomatically gain EXP# based on your character's level.

name: Unity Training Center Entrance Charm (24 hours)
desc: This charm grants you the power to enter the #cUnity Training Center within Mu Lung Dojo# where you #cautomatically gain EXP# based on your character's level.

name: 13th Anniversary Premium PC Cafe Coin
desc:
A Premium PC Cafe Coin issued for the 13th Anniversary. 
It can be sold for a special price to #cNPC Gold Richie at Free Market Entrance.#

#cGold Richie Purchase Period: Until TKTKTK QRQRQR.

name: Sub-Zero Hunt Trial Pass
desc: A pass that restores the #cmonster population# of the #cSub-Zero Hunt# to 3,000 for free when you give it to #cFrappe.#

name: Hunter's Arena Coupon
desc: A coupon that recharges the #cnumber of huntable monsters# to 500 when you give it to #cCassandra# at the #cHunter's Arena#.

name: Intense Power Crystal
desc: A soul crystal left behind by someone with intense power. The crystal is divided equally amongst party members. Has no special function, but you can sell it at a high price to a \r#Collector# who hangs out at the \r#Free Market Entrance#. But remember, the Collector only purchases \r#set quantities during specific time frames#.

name: Gold Richie Coin
desc: A Gold Richie commemorative coin. You can sell it for 7 Million Mesos if you take it to #cGold Richie# at the Free Market Entrance. You can find out #when you can sell these by talking to Gold Richie.

name: Stone Origin Droplet
desc: This bit of Esferan Erda has formed into a magical stone droplet.

name: Stone Cobweb Droplet
desc: This magical stone droplet is filled with Will's power.

name: Spark of Determination
desc: A spark filled with the willpower of the warriors of the Alliance. Take the Spark of Determination and the Shadow of Annihilation to Lorelei to obtain an object that'll help open the path to the Black Mage.

name: Shadow of Annihilation
desc: A vile fragment of power acquired from defeating Verus Hilla. Within this churning chaos you can feel the essence of the Black Mage. Take the Spark of Determination and the Shadow of Annihilation to Lorelei to obtain an object that'll help open the path to the Black Mage.

name: Fragment of Destiny
desc: An extraordinary fragment earned by following the Journey of Destiny. You must have this to gain access to the Black Mage's inner sanctum.

name: Blue Flame
desc: This scorchingly hot blue flame might just set fire to anything it comes into contact with.

name: Mighty Jewel Powder
desc: Strength-infused powdered jewels. Collect several to exchange for a Magical Jewel Box.

name: Lucky Jewel Powder
desc: Luck-infused powdered jewels. Collect several to exchange for a Magical Jewel Box.

name: Keen Jewel Powder
desc: Wisdom-infused powdered jewels. Collect several to exchange for a Magical Jewel Box.

name: Nimble Jewel Powder
desc: Dexterity-infused powdered jewels. Collect several to exchange for a Magical Jewel Box.

name: Straw Voodoo Doll
desc: A doll made out of straw.

name: Wooden Voodoo Doll
desc: A doll made out of wood.

name: Piece of Secret Book
desc: Everybody wants a piece of this book. It's full of mysterious words.

name: Sage Cat Doll
desc: A stuffed animal with the Sage Cat's soul trapped inside.

name: Training Certificate
desc: A training certificate you get for defeating the Master Dummy. It shows you trained for a very long time.

name: Anti-magic Stone
desc: An intact anti-magic stone. You can exchange anti-magic collected in Anti-magic items and stones with Kritias Commemorative Coins.

name: Oak Tree Acorn
desc: A small acorn that squirrels were playing with.

name: Red Porky Thorn
desc: Thorns from Red Porky's back. Ouch!

name: Black Porky Thorn
desc: Thorns from Black Porky's back. Ouch!

name: Snake Skin
desc: Quality snake leather. The snake's patterns are featured clearly on it.

name: Red Flower Serpent Pompom
desc: A flower off of a Red Flower Serpent.

name: Giant Centipede Marble
desc: A red marble from a Giant Centipede.

name: Trainee's Belt
desc: A belt given to bears at the beginning of their training.

name: Broken Antler
desc: An antler of a White Deer, which you broke off...

name: Nectarine Seed
desc: A seed spat out by a Peach Monkey.

name: Apprentice's Belt
desc: Only experienced bears are allowed to wear these.

name: Bear Paw
desc: A thick bear paw.

name: Broken Pot Fragmen
desc: A piece of a broken pot.

name: Ginseng Water
desc: A hot pot that contains water that's been boiling with ginseng for a long time.

name: Bellflower
desc: A common bellflower you can find in the mountains.

name: 100-Year-Old Bellflower
desc: A super old bellflower grown to be a hundred years old.

name: Mr. Alli's Alligator Leather
desc: Nice Alligator leather.

name: Marine Map Piece
desc: A piece of a pirate map.

name: Navigation Room Key
desc: Key to the pirates' Navigation Room.

name: Pirates's Voyage Log
desc: A voyage logbook of Lord Pirate's piracy activities

name: Lord Pirate's Hook
desc: Lord Pirate's hand, shaped like a hook.

name: Patrol Robot Memory Card
desc: A Patrol Robot's memory card. It's used to control the Robot.

name: Clean Water Bottle
desc: A water bottle stolen by the Water Thief.

name: Trash Bag
desc: A black trash bag that came out of a Dust Box.

name: Streetlight Structure
desc: A tentacle from the side of a Streetlight.

name: Patrol Robot S Memory Card
desc: A Patrol Robot S's memory card. It's used to control the Robot.

name: Guard Robot E's Memory Chip
desc: Guard Robot E's memory chip. It's used to control the Robot.

name: Trashy Thing
desc: A piece of trash from the Trash Can.

name: Wooden Plank
desc: A wooden board from the Strange Sign.

name: Chubby Serpent Tail
desc: A serpent's chubby tail.

name: Safety First Board
desc: A sign carried by Safety First.

name: Rock Fragment
desc: A rock fragment obtained from Baby Boulder Muncher.

name: Ore Fragment
desc: A rock fragment obtained from Big Boulder Muncher. Looks like this can be carved into a jewel...

name: Boulder Shield
desc: A strong shield made from rocks.

name: Shovel
desc: A work shovel carried by Racoco.

name: Big Spider Antenna
desc: The antenna of a Big Spider.

name: Cart
desc: A cart pushed around by Cart Bears.

name: Raccoon Tail
desc: A Racaroni's fluffy tail.

name: Safety Hat
desc: A safety hat worn by Raco.

name: Ore Muncher Sample
desc: A sample taken from an Ore Muncher.

name: Flaming Rue
desc: Rare Rue ore imbued with the heat and pressure of the underground.

name: Guard Robot L's Memory Chip
desc: Guard Robot L's memory chip. It's used to control the robot.

name: Security System Deactivation Key
desc: A card key that can be used to deactivate the Security System.

name: Security System Parts
desc: Parts that make up the Enhanced Security System.

name: Filament Lightbulb
desc: A broken bulb from the head of an Android.

name: Android Parts
desc: Broken parts from an Android.

name: Poison Gas
desc: Poison Gas created from a Poison Gas Generator.

name: Futuroid Part 1
desc: One of the many parts needed to make a Futuroid. Bring all 7 parts to Gaga along with an Electronic Heart. You can get a permanent version of the Electronic Heart from Gachapons, and a limited version from Nack in Ardentmill. \r\n

name: Futuroid Part 2
desc: One of the many parts needed to make a Futuroid. Bring all 7 parts to Gaga along with an Electronic Heart. You can get a permanent version of the Electronic Heart from Gachapons, and a limited version from Nack in Ardentmill. \r\n

name: Futuroid Part 3
desc: One of the many parts needed to make a Futuroid. Bring all 7 parts to Gaga along with an Electronic Heart. You can get a permanent version of the Electronic Heart from Gachapons, and a limited version from Nack in Ardentmill. \r\n

name: Futuroid Part 4
desc: One of the many parts needed to make a Futuroid. Bring all 7 parts to Gaga along with an Electronic Heart. You can get a permanent version of the Electronic Heart from Gachapons, and a limited version from Nack in Ardentmill. \r\n

name: Futuroid Part 5
desc: One of the many parts needed to make a Futuroid. Bring all 7 parts to Gaga along with an Electronic Heart. You can get a permanent version of the Electronic Heart from Gachapons, and a limited version from Nack in Ardentmill. \r\n

name: Futuroid Part 6
desc: One of the many parts needed to make a Futuroid. Bring all 7 parts to Gaga along with an Electronic Heart. You can get a permanent version of the Electronic Heart from Gachapons, and a limited version from Nack in Ardentmill. \r\n

name: Futuroid Part 7
desc: One of the many parts needed to make a Futuroid. Bring all 7 parts to Gaga along with an Electronic Heart. You can get a permanent version of the Electronic Heart from Gachapons, and a limited version from Nack in Ardentmill. \r\n

name: Gelatin Blob
desc: A transparent blob of gelatin. Do not eat.

name: Red Megran Fruit
desc: A red fruit from Megran that is used as a rare medicine ingredient.

name: Rumo Leaf
desc: A rare leaf from Rumo. It's full of life, but loses it the more you handle it.

name: Test Flask
desc: A flask used for all kinds of fancy science-looking things.

name: Purple Liquid
desc: Unidentified purple liquid that might be toxic. Or delicious. Hard to tell.

name: Steel Fragment
desc: Iron Mutae are covered in this stuff.

name: Reinforced Steel Fragment
desc: Just try breaking this steel. I dare you.

name: Mithril Fragment
desc: This came from a Mithril Mutae, probably not by choice.

name: Reinforced Mithril Fragment
desc: Was part of a Reinforced Mithril Mutae, before you decided to recycle it.

name: Decayed Scorpion Stinger
desc: This scorpion stinger has seen better days.

name: Test Beaker
desc: A beaker that just REEKS of science.

name: Clean Dew
desc: You need this for Homunculus Alchemy. No one knows why.

name: Magic Blood
desc: Extracted from a Homunculus. The enchantments have the ability to reveal truths.

name: Alchemy Stone
desc: A mystical stone forged by alchemy. It's a pretty safe bet that it contains some kind of power.

name: Decayed Wasp Stinger
desc: A nasty old stinger. Still looks dangerous.

name: Tangled Wires
desc: Don't shock yourself!

name: Plug
desc: Even Neo Huroids need to be plugged in.

name: Broken Iron Heart
desc: A broken mechanical heart. It looks like it can be repaired and used again, if it can work through its issues.

name: Poacher Certificate
desc: Poachers carry these certificates around to tell each other apart.

name: Soft Cottons
desc: This Teddy Bear really spilled his guts.

name: Cute Panda Doll
desc: Looks just like a real panda!

name: Youngest Duckie
desc: A cute toy duck on wheels. Look at it go!

name: Plastic Toy Sword
desc: A toy soldier's plastic sword. Somewhat less effective than you current weapon.

name: Robo Battery
desc: Still has a little juice left in it.

name: Master Robo Battery
desc: Custom batteries are such a pain to replace.

name: Targa Paw
desc: Targa's foot. Ew!

name: Small Spring
desc: A tiny spring of a clock. Couldn't be THAT important.

name: Table Clock
desc: This thing just keeps on ticking.

name: Small Cog
desc: Just another cog in the machine...

name: Small Springy Worm
desc: A worm that feeds on time. Maybe it's a metaphor...

name: Clock Spring Component
desc: Grandpa Clock's still got some old springs kicking around. He really should get with the times.

name: Sealed Teddy
desc: This teddy bear is like a luxury suite for ghosts. For children 2 and up!

name: Shackled Paw
desc: This teddy paw was holding another teddy. It's bears all the way down.

name: Broken Teddy
desc: This plushy used to be possessed by a ghost. Don't worry, the ghost is gone. Probably.

name: Freed Spirit
desc: A spirit from the Soul Teddy. Looks pretty happy to be free.

name: Giant Grandpa Clock
desc: Big and unwieldy. Watches have come a long way from this.

name: Piece of Time
desc: You know how people always wish for more time? Well, here's your chance!

name: Colorful Hat
desc: Hat. Colorful. Good.

name: Hat Dealie-Bobber
desc: This ball popped right off of Lazy Buffy's hat. Like everything else in Maple World, it looks like it holds a mysterious power.

name: Alishar's Key
desc: How's Alishar supposed to get into his car now?!

name: Ghost Pirate Wheel
desc: Looks like those Ghost Pirates won't be going anywhere in a hurry.

name: Dual Ghost Pirate Wheel
desc: Good job dooming the Dual Ghost Pirates to drift aimlessly for eternity.

name: Klock's Broken Clock
desc: Still right twice a day.

name: Dark Klock's Broken Clock
desc: Still right twice a day. But only about evil things.

name: Viking's Token
desc: Needed to get into all the coolest Viking parties.

name: Viking Helm
desc: You can smell the mead and sweat on this thing from a mile away.

name: Frozen Time
desc: Should still be good if you thaw it out.

name: Time Jar
desc: This can keep the Phantom Watch bottled up.

name: Damaged Hourglass
desc: It looks broken, but the sand doesn't spill out. Mysterious!

name: Memory Cloth
desc: The official colors of the Memory Monks.

name: Memory Cone Hat
desc: A hat that is worn by Memory Monk Trainees. Obviously a mark of respect.

name: Memory Helm
desc: A hat that is worn by Memory Guardians. Helps keep the memories in.

name: Memory Heart
desc: Heart of the Chief Memory Guardian. Doesn't he need this?

name: Dodo Helm
desc: The Whale of Time is rather fond of this hat.

name: Qualm Cloth
desc: The official colors of the Qualm Monks.

name: Qualm Cone Hat
desc: A hat that is worn by Qualm Monk Trainees. They have no qualms with it.

name: Qualm Helm
desc: A hat that is worn by Qualm Guardians. Keeps them qualm.

name: Qualm Heart
desc: Heart of the Chief Qualm Guardian. Kinda gross when you think about it.

name: Lilynouch Mask
desc: Protects the identity of Lilynouch, the Ice Knight.

name: Oblivion Cloth
desc: The official colors of the Oblivion Monks.

name: Oblivion Cone Hat
desc: A hat that is worn by Oblivion Monk Trainees. They seem oblivious to it.

name: Oblivion Helm
desc: A hat that is worn by Oblivion Guardians. Protects from oblivion-related injuries.

name: Oblivion Heart
desc: Heart of the Chief Oblivion Guardian. He might want it back at some point.

name: Lyka's Horn
desc: Not the kind you play.

name: Kentaurus King Flame
desc: A royal source of power.

name: Griffey's Broken Horn
desc: A noble Griffey horn. Great for making jewelry.

name: Fibo's Head
desc: The head of Fibo. Collect 6 different parts, the Administrator will purify them.

name: Fibo's Body
desc: The body of Fibo. Collect 6 different parts, the Administrator will purify them.

name: Fibo's Right Arm
desc: The right arm of Fibo. Collect 6 different parts, the Administrator will purify them.

name: Fibo's Left Arm
desc: The left arm of Fibo. Collect 6 different parts, the Administrator will purify them.

name: Fibo's Right Leg
desc: The right leg of Fibo. Collect 6 different parts, the Administrator will purify them.

name: Fibo's Left Leg
desc: The right leg of Fibo. Collect 6 different parts, the Administrator will purify them.

name: Broken Blade (Blue)
desc: This would probably make a great weapon if it was still whole. Look at all those icy runes...

name: Broken Hilt (Blue)
desc: Imagine the weapon that must have been attached to this frozen thing.

name: Broken Shaft (Blue)
desc: All that's missing is the ball. Maybe it melted. Too bad that's the important part.

name: Broken Bow (Blue)
desc: Even as busted up as it is, this bow looks like it could shoot some wicked frosty arrows.

name: Broken Feather (Blue)
desc: Somehow this feather is as cold and heavy as a gigantic block of ice. Magic!

name: Broken Blade (Red)
desc: The runes on this thing are hot to the touch. What kind of weapon was it...?

name: Broken Hilt (Red)
desc: Despite the wrappings, this hilt is almost too hot to handle.

name: Broken Shaft (Red)
desc: Even without the ball, this thing is hot enough to do some damage.

name: Broken Bow (Red)
desc: You can tell by the markings that this bow used to shoot some white-hot arrows.

name: Broken Feather (Red)
desc: A decorative feather that's both hot and as heavy as a burning rock.

name: Broken Blade (Black)
desc: You're not sure what the runes on this say, but you get the feeling it's nothing good.

name: Broken Hilt (Black)
desc: This hilt feels terrible and threatening, despite not having anything dangerous attached to it.

name: Broken Shaft (Black)
desc: It's just a chain and a shaft, but they radiate such a sense of dread...

name: Broken Bow (Black)
desc: You can feel the agony of lost souls shot through with this ancient bow. Creepy.

name: Broken Feather (Black)
desc: A feather that weighs much more than it looks. It's also totally evil.

name: Basic Magician's Cloth
desc: Even cheap cloth like this is infused with magic. You can't throw a rock without hitting a magical artifact, it seems.

name: Intermediate Magician's Cloth
desc: This dark fabric radiates mysterious power. That makes sense, considering its intended use.

name: Advanced Magician's Cloth
desc: A piece of mysterious fabric surrounded by black energy. Guess evil magic is pretty popular these days.

name: Hawk Claw
desc: A sharp claw from a poacher's hawk.

name: Grave Robber Certificate
desc: Grave robbers carry these certificates around to tell each other apart.

name: Hunting Dog's Fang
desc: A fang from the grave robber's hunting dogs. Seems sharp enough to pierce anything.

name: Neon Bat Wings
desc: A pair of glowing wings from a Neon Bat. Might work like a flashlight in the dark.

name: Glowing Primary Rock Fragment
desc: A fragment of a glowing primary rock.

name: Spirit Substance
desc: A curious substance from a Peace Spirit.

name: Darkness Fragment
desc: This piece of darkness is thick with shadow.

name: Omen's Fragment
desc: You feel the same mysterious energy in this that you felt from the Omen.

name: Master Omen's Fragment
desc: You feel the same mysterious energy in this that you felt from the Master Omen.

name: Demolisher Part
desc: A part from the Barrier Demolisher.

name: Surveillance Robot Memory Chip
desc: This memory chip is all that's left of a Surveillance Robot.

name: Frozen Rose Petal
desc: A rose petal frozen from centuries in the snow. Doesn't seem tasty, so you might as well sell it at the shop.

name: Loose Chain
desc: An old chain that clangs around in your inventory. All that noise is making you mad. You should sell it at the shop.

name: Dried Rose Vine
desc: A dried rose vine. It makes the Golems look a bit prettier.

name: Shiny Flower Powder
desc: Shining bees drop  these shining powders. Maybe the shops will take this shiny thing for a lot of money.

name: Suspicious Lime Powder
desc: When you watch them closely, you can see that these lime powders are moving by themselves. Suspicious!

name: Apple
desc: It's produced in farms around the Veracent Village.

name: Grapes
desc: They're produced in farms around the Veracent Village.

name: Samuel's Ingredient
desc: Samuel's Ingredient

name: Weird thing
desc: Not sure what it is. He wants 30 of them.

name: Something weird
desc: Sonia said it's proof that I shouldn't believe Gilbert.

name: His Trace
desc: The Courage Statue said I would know who he was when I got the 'hint'. He's a liar.

name: Invitation Letter
desc: It just says "Welcome". How lame.

name: Talisman
desc: The Wisdom Statue said it would help defeate Vale. Not sure.

name: Rare Treasure
desc: A treasure that Icy Blue Kerberos has. I can hardly believe it.

name: Life is
desc: A note that says "Life is".

name: C
desc: A note that says "C".

name: between
desc: A note that says "between".

name: B
desc: A note that says "B".

name: and
desc: A note that says "and".

name: D
desc: A note that says "D".

name: Trace of Courage
desc: A manifested trace of courage.

name: Lost Toy
desc: A toy for children.

name: Happy Seed
desc: This seed is believed to generate happy energy, and hated by monsters due to its distinctive odor.

name: Treasure Chest Key
desc: An old key that opens a treasure chest.

name: Shiny Crystal
desc: A remarkably shiny crystal.

name: Blood Pirate Emblem
desc: An emblem earned from defeating the Captain Blood Pirates.

name: Siren's Talon
desc: Claws left behind by a Siren. Very sharp.

name: Coral Bit
desc: A bit of coral that has broken free from a coral reef.

name: Ocean Rock
desc: A shard of ocean rock that broke free from a reef.

name: Cat Mask
desc: A mask worn by Coastal Cats.

name: Cat Claws
desc: A Gray Tomcat's claws.

name: Broken Delfino Sword
desc: A broken one-handed Delfino sword.

name: Broken Delfino Goggles
desc: A pair of broken Delfino goggles.

name: Broken Delfino Staff
desc: A broken Delfino staff.

name: Broken Delfino Claw
desc: A broken Delfino claw.

name: Broken Delfino Spear
desc: A broken Delfino spear.

name: Ripped Cloak
desc: A fragment from Riverson's cloak.

name: Brown Furball
desc: A ball of fur from a brown wolf.

name: Blue Furball
desc: A ball of fur from a blue wolf.

name: Blue Pirate Hat
desc: A blue hat that Dawnveil pirates wear.

name: Red Pirate Hat
desc: A red hat that Dawnveil pirates wear.

name: Nightwhip
desc: A whip used by Guild Assassins.

name: Nightcutter
desc: A blade used by Guild Assassins.

name: Nightrobe
desc: A robe worn by Guild Assassins.

name: Red Scarf Scrap
desc: A scrap from the scarf worn by Il Capo.

name: Dried Caterpillar
desc: Dried caterpillar jerky. It's a yummy food for baby foxes.

name: Spotted Wings
desc: These are the wings of a ladybug. They make good meals for baby foxes.

name: Sparrow Egg
desc: An egg stolen from a sparrow's nest. It makes a delicious treat for foxes.

name: Mouse Tail
desc: A tail from a Balloon Mouse. It's a yummy fox treat.

name: Red Frog Legs
desc: Frog legs from a Red Poison Frog. Be careful, they're poisonous all over.

name: Green Frog Legs
desc: Frog legs from a Green Poison Frog. Be careful, it's poisonous all over.

name: Mohawk Feather
desc: A fuzzy feather from a Delinquent Chick. It's covered in rebellious hair wax.

name: Rocker Feather
desc: A fuzzy feather from a Punk Chick. It's covered in hard rock hair wax.

name: Mane Fur
desc: Fur from a hyena's back. Nice spots.

name: Fang
desc: A long fang from a hyena. It symbolizes bravery, because someone had to go in there to get it.

name: Rock-Paper-Scissors Ticket
desc: This sloppy Rock-Paper-Scissors Ticket says #c'teeket'#. Lil Zakum needs some spelling lessons.

name: Ancient Evil Eye Tail
desc: A tail of an Evil Eye that used to live in the Ancient Cave. It's glossy and lustrous, unlike the tails of those other loser Evil Eyes.

name: Clockwise Labyrinth Key
desc: Drop it on the portal in the room to rotate the room's destination once clockwise.

name: Red Sand Powder
desc: Red Sand Powder dropped by a Red Sand Dwarf. Used to explore the 29th floor of the Tower of Oz. If you gather 10 Red Sand Powders, a Red Sand Crystal will appear beneath a tree on the left.

name: Counterclockwise Labyrinth Key
desc: Drop it on the portal in the room to rotate the room's destination once counterclockwise.

name: Yellow Leather
desc: A piece of yellow leather dropped by a Yellow Curly Cow. It's thin and light and doesn't tear easily. It would be great for clothing, but you have to use it to open the portal.

name: Purple Leather
desc: A piece of purple leather dropped by a Purple Curly Cow. It's a bit thick, but still looks luxurious. Get enough to escape the floor.

name: Orange Slime Liquid
desc: A substance from an Orange Ancient Slime. Gather 10 of this stuff and drop them on the Burning Altar to summon an Orange Ancient Slime.

name: Ancient Blue Turtle Egg
desc: An Ancient Blue Turtle's egg. Would make quite an omelet.

name: Ancient Orange Turtle Egg
desc: An Ancient Orange Turtle's egg. Would make quite a breakfast.

name: Gold Richie Figure
desc: A really cheesy figurine of Gold Richie, but you need it for the Gold Richie's Safe Event.

name: Gold Richie Figure
desc: A really cheesy figurine of Gold Richie, but you need it for the Gold Richie's Safe Event.

name: Gold Richie Figure
desc: A really cheesy figurine of Gold Richie, but you need it for the Gold Richie's Safe Event.

name: Gold Richie Figure
desc: A really cheesy figurine of Gold Richie, but you need it for the Gold Richie's Safe Event.

name: Skeledog's Bone
desc: A mysterious bone. You might be able to make a spicy soup with this bone.\r\n\r\nIt's one of the ingredients for the delicious lunch, and #cif you have 3 of them regardless of type, you will be able to make a delicious lunch by double clicking them.#Do not be afraid, go ahead!

name: The Key
desc: It's a Heart Key which allows you to open the hearts of people who are eating lunch. You could use it to have people change their mind.\r\n\r\nIt's one of the ingredients for the delicious lunch, and #cif you have 3 of them regardless of type, you will be able to make a delicious lunch by double clicking them.#Do not be afraid and go ahead!

name: Dinoram Tenderloin
desc: A thick meat loaf. It looks delicious.\r\n\r\nIt's one of the ingredients for the delicious lunch, and #cif you have 3 of them regardless of type, you will be able to make a delicious lunch by double clicking them.#Do not be afraid and go ahead!

name: Tough Dragon Skin
desc: Very tough monster meat. It's really hard to chew and it tastes like squid.\r\n\r\nIt's one of the ingredients for the delicious lunch, and #cif you have 3 of them regardless of type, you will be able to make a delicious lunch by double clicking them.#Do not be afraid and go ahead!

name: Balrog's Seal Stone
desc: An Evil Spirit Seal Stone. Am I getting controlled by this stone?\r\n\r\nIt's one of the ingredients for the delicious lunch, and #cif you have 3 of them regardless of type, you will be able to make a delicious lunch by double clicking them.#Do not be afraid and go ahead!

name: Poisonous Mushroom
desc: A colorful mushroom. Let's hope it's not poisonous\r\n\r\nIt's one of the ingredients for the delicious lunch, and #cif you have 3 of them regardless of type, you will be able to make a delicious lunch by double clicking them.#Do not be afraid and go ahead!

name: Leaf
desc: It's very fresh, just fresh.\r\n\r\nIt's one of the ingredients for the delicious lunch, and #cif you have 3 of them regardless of type, you will be able to make a delicious lunch by double clicking them.#Do not be afraid and go ahead!

name: Evil Eye Tail
desc: A monster's tentacle. It looks disgusting, but some say it's pretty delicious.\r\n\r\nIt's one of the ingredients for the delicious lunch, and #cif you have 3 of them regardless of type, you will be able to make a delicious lunch by double clicking them.#Do not be afraid and go ahead!

name: Free Spirit
desc: The soul of a bear. This food will literally have 'soul' if you cook with this.r\n\r\nIt's one of the ingredients for the delicious lunch, and #cif you have 3 of them regardless of type, you will be able to make a delicious lunch by double clicking them.#Do not be afraid and go ahead!

name: Chicken Leg
desc: A chicken Leg from Von Bon. It's pretty big.\r\n\r\nIt's one of the ingredients for the delicious lunch, and #cif you have 3 of them regardless of type, you will be able to make a delicious lunch by double clicking them.#Do not be afraid and go ahead!

name: Ticket
desc: It's a Wood Theme Park Ticket. Deliver it to Penya.

name: Fake Ticket
desc: It's a paper that looks like a Wood Theme Park Ticket. The quality is too bad to use as a ticket.

name: Tears of Time
desc: Element earned from mirror world.  You get power by bringing it to the 'Sanctun of Time' then praying

name: Hermes Cube Fragment
desc: Take 10 Hermes Cube Fragments to Hermes to receive a Hermes Cube.

name: Mimiana Egg
desc: An egg of Mimiana, the Mount for knights. Watch the egg grow into a full-grown Mimiana by sharing your experiences with it. Once it matures into a full-grown creature, take it to Kiridu the Mount Trainer.

name: Glass Incubator
desc: A glass incubator where Mimiana is stored. Drag the food into the incubator to feed Mimiana. Once it matures, take it back to Kiridu the Mount Trainer.

stats.3: Mimiana's color has changed completely and its eyes have become more pronounced.  It seems the Mimiana is all grown up.  Let's go ask Kenta for his Supplements.
stats.name: Mimiana's Glass Incubator

name: Mimiana Egg
desc: An egg of Mimiana, the Mount for knights. Watch the egg grow into a full-grown Mimiana by sharing your experiences with it. Once it matures into a full-grown creature, take it to Kiridu the Mount Trainer.

stats.0: It's a new Mimiana egg.
stats.2: Mimiana's head is out.
stats.3: Mimiana just hatched out of the egg.  Let's go report to Kiridu, the Mount Trainer.
stats.name: Mimiana Egg

name: Mind of Maple Necklace
desc: A Mind of Maple Necklace that brings luck and hope to anyone who wears it.

stats.2: 2 pieces of Mind of Maple have been set. The restoring Mind of Maple began to flash a dim light.
stats.3: 3 pieces of Mind of Maple have been set. The fully awakened Mind of Maple began to flash a dim light.
stats.name: Mind of Maple

name: Portrait of an Orange Mushroom
desc: Drawing paper on which you can draw a portrait of an Orange Mushroom. The portrait of an Orange Mushroom can be completed by using the Amazing, Mystical, or Magical watercolor paint on it. \r\n#cCan be opened by double-clicking on it with the mouse.#

name: Portrait of an Octopus
desc: Drawing paper on which you can draw a portrait of an Octopus. The portrait of an Octupus can be completed by using the Amazing, Mystical, or Magical watercolor paint on it. \r\n#cCan be opened by double-clicking on it with the mouse.#

name: Portrait of a Yeti
desc: Drawing paper on which you can draw a portrait of a Yeti. The portrait of a Yeti can be completed by using the Amazing, Mystical, or Magical watercolor paint on it. \r\n#cCan be opened by double-clicking on it with the mouse.#

name: Hanging Scroll
desc: A Hanging Scroll given to you by the Black Wing Shadow Warrior. The erased content can be restored by using special ink.\r\n#cCan be opened by double-clicking on it with a mouse.#

stats.2: A scroll with faint writing that is slightly visible.
stats.3: A scroll with faint writing that is somewhat visible.
stats.4: The writing on the scroll has been completely restored, but the message seems unusual. Take it to Mr. Do.
stats.name: Scroll

name: Dirty Treasure Map
desc: A treasure map given by Kyrin. There are three sections--red, green, and white--that are invisible. The green section should be cleaned first. \r\n\r\n*If you don't need the item anymore, just go to Jack in the Top Floor - Hallway to discard it.#

stats.2: The seal is released and the red part is erased!
stats.3: When you pour ink on it, a hidden picture appears and the map is completed!
stats.name: Dirty Treasure Map

name: Socks Frame
desc: Double click on the item to open the UI to add knitting balls to make the Christmas socks.

stats.2: It looks almost like Christmas Socks.
stats.3: Wala!  You have successully made Christmas Socks!
stats.name: My Socks

name: Gold Box
desc: A gold treasure chest dropped by a monster. This can be opened with the Gold Master Key available at the Cash Shop. If you already have the Master Key, just double-click the box to open it.

name: Bummer Effect
desc: This effect is for people who helped Lazy Daisy but failed to hatch the egg. You can turn it ON/OFF by double-clicking the icon or using the key configuration menu to assign a shortcut key.

name: Golden Chicken Effect
desc: Golden Chicken Effect was given as a reward for helping Lazy Daisy. You can turn it ON/OFF by double-clicking the icon or using the key configuration menu to assign a shortcut key.

desc: A beautiful card with season's greetings. Double click on it to read!
